Facenet_GAIS --- Installation documentation¶

Want to download and start our AWESOME Facenet Project but don't know where to start¶

Let us begin -¶

prerequisite - try with python later versions - 3.8+¶

  • Download and install python
    • https://docs.python.org/3.6/using/windows.html#installing-python
    • https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3lGhtIqT0Tk

First visit our link -

https://github.com/mlpocprojects/mlsecurity_app/

Click on the "Code" Button and copy the code underneath¶

Now open command Git Bash on your device and -¶

* Change the current working directory to the location where you want the cloned directory
* Type **git clone**, and then paste the URL you copied earlier 
      - $ git clone (URL for repo)

Now let us open the directory you have created.¶

Install requirement.txt on cmd, terminal or command prompt, with the help of following command -¶

pip install -r requirements.txt¶

Once the requirements are installed add user (or your) images you want to recognise in the "images" folder¶

images Format to add image of yours or User images.¶

Face_Recong

images

Alice

Alice1.jpg

Alice2.jpg

Bob

Bob.jpg

Now run the file in CMD -¶

> cd deepface¶

> python Runner.py¶

And done, you can now run the Facenet Project on your device¶

THANK YOU¶
